ğŸ” Safety Strategy for New Additions
We will:

âœ… 1. Use Unique Container/Image Names
Use prefixes like:

gender-mlflow

gender-airflow-webserver

gender-airflow-scheduler

gender-postgres

gender-jenkins

gender-k8s-deploy (if needed)

âœ… 2. Assign Non-Conflicting Ports
Avoid these already used ports:

5000 â€“ already taken by both MLflow-1 & gender-classifier Flask app

8080, 5001, 8501 â€” already used by existing services

For new services, we can safely use:

MLflow UI: 5500

Airflow Webserver: 5800

PostgreSQL (if needed): 5433

Flask alt port (if parallel run needed): 5050

Jenkins (alt): 5055

âœ… 3. Use Separate Docker Volumes & Networks
We'll use new named volumes like:

gender_mlflow_artifacts

gender_airflow_db_volume

And a dedicated Docker network:

gender_pipeline_net

